---
fruits:
  - "apple"
  - "banana"
  - "cherry"
users:
  - name: "Dash"
    role: "admin"
  - name: "Sparky"
    role: "editor"
  - name: "Dino"
    role: "viewer"
matrix:
  -
    - 1
    - 2
  -
    - 3
    - 4
empty: []
prefix: "> "
showUsers: true
---

Basic list iteration:
{{ for fruit in fruits }}* {{ fruit }}
{{ /for }}
Object property access:
{{ for user in users }}{{ user.name }} ({{ user.role }})
{{ /for }}
Nested loops:
{{ for row in matrix }}[{{ for cell in row }}{{ cell }} {{ /for }}]
{{ /for }}
Empty list produces no output:
{{ for item in empty }}never{{ /for }}
Access outer scope:
{{ for fruit in fruits }}{{ prefix }}{{ fruit }}
{{ /for }}
For inside if:
{{ if showUsers }}{{ for user in users }}  - {{ user.name }}
{{ /for }}{{ /if }}
Inline with the surrounding text:
Items: {{ for fruit in fruits }}{{ fruit }}, {{ /for }}done.
